Okay, so we've looked at the practical stuff, the pros and cons. But this debate goes even deeper. It gets into a more philosophical question, really. What's the ultimate goal of the school schedule? Is it to optimize the day for learning right now, based on biology? Or is it about preparing students for what comes next?

00:06:30.000 --> 00:07:00.000
And you can really see those two competing goals right here. On one side, the argument for later starts is all about prioritizing a teenager's biological needs to improve their health and focus. Makes sense. But on the other side, the argument for earlier starts is also pretty compelling. It's about building real-world responsibility and time management skills.

